<td>Craig Turk, Jill Goldsmith &amp; David E. Kelley</td>
<td>Mike Listo</td>
<td>2008-04-30</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="description" style="border-bottom:3px solid #DDA97E" colspan="6">When Shirley's nephew, a Democrat delegate, refuses to vote for Clinton despite her winning the popular vote in Massachusetts, Alan and Shirley sue the Democratic National Party to try and halt the abuse of power. Denny falls for a female rancher, Sunny Fields (<a href="/wiki/Christine_Ebersole" title="Christine Ebersole">Christine Ebersole</a>) and asks Sack to represent her against the FDA to prevent the sale of cloned meat.&#160;</td>
</tr>
<tr class="vevent" style="text-align: center; background:#F2F2F2">
<td id="ep87">87</td>
<td>19</td>
