<td>David E. Kelley, Jonathan Shapiro, Karen Wyscarver &amp; Sanford Golden</td>
<td>Bill D'Elia</td>
<td>2008-05-21</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="description" style="border-bottom:3px solid #DDA97E" colspan="6">Alan is approached by Judge Harvey Cooper (<a href="/wiki/Anthony_Heald" title="Anthony Heald">Anthony Heald</a>) on behalf of Concord, Massachusetts, who want him to represent them in their attempt to secede from the United States. Alan takes the case, offending Denny, who appears in court representing the United States.&#160;</td>
</tr>
</table>
