</tr>
<tr>
<td class="description" style="border-bottom:3px solid #008080" colspan="6">Alan ignites controversy in the firm when he represents a 15-year-old girl who needs an injunction to get an abortion. Jerry, meanwhile, gets into a fight at a coffee store after an obnoxious patron calls him a "demento".&#160;</td>
</tr>
<tr class="vevent" style="text-align: center; background:#F2F2F2">
<td id="ep97">97</td>
<td>9</td>
<td class="summary" style="text-align: left;">"<b>Kill, Baby, Kill</b>"</td>
<td>Lawrence Broch &amp; David E. Kelley</td>
<td>Bob Yannetti</td>
<td>November 17, 2008</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="description" style="border-bottom:3px solid #008080" colspan="6">At the request of another lawyer, Denny Crane and Carl Sack travel to Virginia to defend a corrections officer who shot a death row inmate out of mercy after his execution went awry. Meanwhile, Alan once again tries to push a relationship with Shirley when they represent a woman, Martha Headly (<a href="/wiki/Cheri_Oteri" title="Cheri Oteri">Cheri Oteri</a>) who was fired for voting for <a href="/wiki/John_McCain" title="John McCain">John McCain</a>.&#160;</td>
</tr>
<tr class="vevent" style="text-align: center; background:#F2F2F2">
<td id="ep98">98</td>
<td>10</td>
<td class="summary" style="text-align: left;">"<b>Thanksgiving</b>"</td>
<td>David E. Kelley</td>
<td>Mike Listo</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="description" style="border-bottom:3px solid #008080" colspan="5">Although she wants a quiet reprieve from the significant financial woes facing the firm, Shirley's intimate Thanksgiving get-together with Carl turns into a dysfunctional family affair when she invites Alan, Denny, Jerry, and Katie -- as well as cocky prosecutor Melvin Palmer, emotionally unstable law partner Edwin Poole (<a href="/wiki/Larry_Miller" title="Larry Miller">Larry Miller</a>) and his nine-year-old foster son, who tried to mug her -- to join them in the feast.&#160;</td>
</tr>
<tr class="vevent" style="text-align: center; background:#F2F2F2">
<td id="ep99">99</td>
<td>11</td>
<td class="summary" style="text-align: left;">"<b>Juiced</b>"</td>
<td>Corinne Brinkerhoff &amp; Susan Dickes &amp; David E. Kelley</td>
<td>Michael Lohmann</td>
<td>December 1, 2008</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="description" style="border-bottom:3px solid #008080" colspan="6">After Denny learns some disturbing news about the progression of his Alzheimer's disease and that an experimental drug which could slow his deterioration is available but not FDA approved, Alan tries to convince the Massachusetts Supreme Court to let his best friend have access to it. Meanwhile the murderous Catherine Piper (<a href="/wiki/Betty_White" title="Betty White">Betty White</a>) returns, and Jerry and Katie take on the case of an ambitious student (<a href="/wiki/Margo_Harshman" title="Margo Harshman">Margo Harshman</a>) fighting to maintain her acceptance to Harvard after being disqualified for using a brain-enhancing drug during her SATs.&#160;</td>
</tr>
<tr class="vevent" style="text-align: center; background:#F2F2F2">
<td id="ep100">100</td>
<td>12</td>
<td class="summary" style="text-align: left;">"<b>Made In China</b>"</td>
<td>David E. Kelley &amp; Susan Dickes &amp; Lauren MacKenzie</td>
<td>Bill D'Elia</td>
<td>December 8, 2008</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="description" style="border-bottom:3px solid #008080" colspan="6">(Part 1) The lawyers arrive at work to discover with horror that Paul has confirmed the firm's merger - but with a Chinese syndicate. While Alan and Shirley lead a charge against their new owners, Shirley prepares for her wedding to Carl; Alan and Jerry prepare for the Supreme Court hearing to let Denny have access to a non-FDA approved drug that could slow down his rapidly progressing Alzheimer's; Jerry and Katie grow closer; and Denny poses an important question to Alan.&#160;</td>
</tr>
<tr class="vevent" style="text-align: center; background:#F2F2F2">
<td id="ep101">101</td>
<td>13</td>
<td class="summary" style="text-align: left;">"<b>Last Call</b>"</td>
<td>David E. Kelley &amp; Susan Dickes</td>
<td>Bill D'Elia</td>
<td>December 8, 2008</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="description" style="border-bottom:3px solid #008080" colspan="6">(Part 2) To ensure his financial and physical safety as his Alzheimer's progresses, Denny proposes marriage to Alan, incurring the wrath of a gay rights group in the process. Paul Lewiston takes over Litigation on behalf of the Chinese owners of the firm, while the lawyers must consider their own futures. Carl and Shirley run into problems in the week leading up to their wedding. Katie and Jerry finally get beyond awkward dates. And, before they can leave for their marriage ceremony at Nimmo Bay, Alan and Denny appear in the Supreme Court.&#160;</td>
</tr>
